500|$|Cher's next albums, I'd Rather <b>Believe</b> <b>in</b> <b>You</b> (1976) and Cherished (1977), {{the latter}} {{a return to}} her pop style at Warner's producers' insistence, were commercially unsuccessful. In 1977, under the rubric [...] "Allman and Woman", she {{recorded}} alongside Allman the duet album Two the Hard Way. Their relationship ended following {{the release of the}} album, and their divorce was finalized in 1979. Beginning in 1978, she had a two-year live-in relationship with Kiss member Gene Simmons. That year, she legally changed her name from Cherilyn Sarkisian La Piere Bono Allman to Cher, to eliminate the use of four surnames. She returned to prime time television with the specials Cher... Special (1978) and Cher... and Other Fantasies (1979).|$|E
